&lt;p&gt;Elastic’s Professional Services team works across every technology and system to deliver solutions for our customers. The &lt;strong&gt;Delivery Manager&lt;/strong&gt; plays a key role in the project delivery of Elastic services and helps ensure our growing customer base receives high-quality, successful implementations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will work with the services team to service our global customers on billable projects. Our customers include Fortune 100 companies, startups, government entities, and nonprofits solving some of the world&#39;s most exciting search, observability, and cybersecurity challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Delivery Manager will be a customer-facing role responsible for &lt;strong&gt;leading project delivery in the region, supporting revenue goals, facilitating communications, meetings, and reporting&lt;/strong&gt;. Success in this role will be measured by customer satisfaction and project delivery outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete Elastic training and become proficient in our Outcome Based Delivery Methodology and practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support engagement execution from start to finish: identifying and mitigating risk, providing status reporting, and managing operational tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Services sellers, architects, consultants, third-party partners, and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to delivery methodology improvements and share lessons learned to enhance our services practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Customer Success and Account Executives to support account renewals and add-on opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a portfolio of multiple engagements, varying in size, through strong prioritization and time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel 20-40% of the time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
